This paper deals with decidability of decision problems in data-enriched models, specifically Petri nets with data. This topic falls under the area of formal methods and theoretical computer science. The paper also mentions the WQO Dichotomy Conjecture, which is a well-known conjecture in the area of order theory. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with graph structures, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of Petri nets suggests sub-categories such as cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
